Description: Fragment of neck and flattened, ridged handle of a pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, light brown; gold mica. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28a, 31 or 175, 10. Unpublished parallels from Samos may be from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1527)
